Problem : Find Nearby Things

SQL Box Query 
  SELECT *
  FROM business
  WHERE lat BETWEEN 12.90 AND 13.00
  AND lon BETWEEN 77.50 AND 77.60;

  Box search, not a true distance search

  CREATE INDEX idx_lat ON business(lat); 
  CREATE INDEX idx_lon ON business(lon);

  SQL indexes are 1D (sorted lists)

  Data is 2D(lat, lon), Indexes are 1D

  SQL cannot efficiently index multi-dimensional proximity using simple indexes

Convert data 2D → 1D 
  Deterministic and Continuous
  Accurate

  Geohash
    Generate GeoHash
      Map Earth to Rectangle
      Generate using 0s and 1s of quadrant of Rectangle
      Encode Binary32 (22 + 10)
  
    Prefix Matching 
      Cons
        Same prefix” ≠ same physical distance
        Boundary Issue
          Some points inside rectangle → farther than expected 
          Some points just outside → closer but missed
  
  
  Google S2
    Generate Cell-Ids
      Map Earth(Sphere) to Cube
      Draw a line from Earth center → Point → extend to cube
      Hilbert curve of Grid
  
    Near by places have closer Cells-Ids

Convert location → tree path
  Quatree
    build in-memory tree structure
    Create a Note for Lat and Long 
    Split in 4 quadrant until meet criteria

    leaf node
      lat & lon 
      100 Buisness ID

    Internal node
      lat, lon, 
      4 child nodes

    L = 3I + 1
    High Server Up time


Data Storage
(lat, lon) → cell_id (Geohash / S2)
business_id → cell_id
INDEX(cell_id)

Query Time
user(lat, lon) → user_cell
user_cell → list_of_cells (covering radius R)

Fetch
SELECT *
FROM business
WHERE cell_id IN (list_of_cells)
    
